		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30540413">Recently I've watched Ghost in the Shell SAC 2nd GIG and was blown away by the depth of the narrative and the mystery, the action, the character development of guys like Batou on episodes like TRANSPARENT, as well as the music. I've also seen both of Oshii's film adaptations, which are as most people know, extremely different in presentation as well as theme to a degree. <br />
<br />
While Oshii's series is very heavy on philosophy of AI other typical cyberpunk themes (I say typical but of course it is very deep and interesting), Stand Alone Complex seems to explore subjects such as social phenomenon more than anything. Considering which one is the best adaptation, I find myself at an impasse. Surely both have their merits, but if a person could only go to one adaptation, which would it be?<br />
<br />
On a side note is the manga any good? Doesn't quite look like it has enough pages to rival the depth of the animations.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
