		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30542223">I think I prefer the films in terms of an 'experience'. If that makes sense.<br />
I need to re-watch both SAC series, though.<br />
<br />
Both films have an atmosphere that surpasses just about any other anime I have seen. The level of detail in the environment, the shots, the sounds. It just comes together so perfectly and is immersive like nothing else.<br />
Innocence has one of my favourite scenes in any film ever - where Batou walks into the convenience store. I have never felt so overwhelmed by the sheer lack of noise before. On a technical level both films are near unmatched.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
