		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30542557">Big Simo I agree with your praise of Oshii's films, although as some would have it, it is stifled under the weight of its own substance, especially Innocence, whereas Stand Alone Complex is able to deliver similar depth in the forms of other areas of philosophy. Personally I was extremely enthralled in certain characters such as Godoh, and social theory like the entire copies without an original thing. The degree to which they take both of these things really is amazing. More than anything, it just interested me. That goes for both sub-universes as well.<br />
<br />
As it so happens I am watching Solid State Society at this very moment, will come back when I finish and post my thoughts and how well it compliments the rest of Stand Alone Complex.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
