		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30557921">Stand Alone Complex all the way.<br />
The movies have a great animation, atmosphere and action, the philosophy is not anywhere near as groundbreaking as it's claimed to be, the stories are pretty simple, the characters are as flat as it can get (only on Innocence that there's an actual character: Batou), the setting is barely explored and the pacing of the first movie is so rushed it hurts my eyes.<br />
But Stand Alone Complex is what a real story looks like. The characters get actual characterization, the stories are amazing and multi-layered mysteries with politics, social commentary and cyberpunk philosophy, the world is great, creative and full of history, and the action is as good as in the movies.<br />
<br />
The best option is watching everything, but since you're hypothesizing "if a person could only go to one adaptation", then it's certainly Stand Alone Complex.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=35120"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://i.imgur.com/MkmghXm.jpg" /></a></div></td>
